---
const SITE_NAME = "The-Circle";
const DISCORD_INVITE = "https://discord.gg/YOURINVITECODE"; // <-- replace this
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>About • {SITE_NAME}</title>
    <meta name="description" content="What The-Circle is, who it’s for, and how it works." />
  </head>

  <body>
    <header class="top">
      <div class="container nav">
        <a class="brand" href="/">
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>{SITE_NAME}</span>
        </a>

        <nav class="links">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <a class="pill" href={DISCORD_INVITE} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Join Discord</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
      <section class="card">
        <h1>About {SITE_NAME}</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          {SITE_NAME} is a Discord that isn’t centered around a product, a creator, or one specific game.
          It exists for one reason: to be a reliable place you can drop into when you want company.
        </p>

        <div class="grid">
          <div class="tile">
            <h2>Who it’s for</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>People who are on Discord a lot and want a chill “home base”</li>
              <li>Anyone who wants to chat, game, or watch something without pressure</li>
              <li>Folks who prefer smaller servers that feel human</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tile">
            <h2>Who it’s not for</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Drama farming, harassment, or being weird to people</li>
              <li>Spammy self-promo servers</li>
              <li>“Be active every day or else” communities</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>What makes it different</h2>
        <p class="text">
          A lot of “friends servers” are chaotic and half-built. A lot of big servers are loud and impersonal.
          The-Circle is set up intentionally — clean channels, solid moderation, good voice quality, and optional private rooms —
          so it’s actually usable as a hangout.
        </p>

        <div class="cta">
          <a class="btn primary" href={DISCORD_INVITE} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Join the Discord</a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="/">Back to Home</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <style>
      :global(body){
        margin:0;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,.92);
        background:
          radial-gradient(900px 500px at 15% 10%, rgba(120,170,255,.22), transparent 60%),
          radial-gradient(800px 450px at 85% 15%, rgba(140,255,190,.16), transparent 55%),
          radial-gradient(700px 450px at 55% 95%, rgba(255,170,120,.12), transparent 55%),
          #0b0f14;
      }
      a{ color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
      .container{ max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 18px; }

      .top{
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        background: rgba(11,15,20,.55);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.10);
        z-index: 10;
      }
      .nav{
        display:flex;
        align-items:center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 14px 18px;
      }
      .brand{
        display:flex;
        gap:10px;
        align-items:center;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }
      .dot{
        width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 999px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,.85);
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px rgba(255,255,255,.08);
      }
      .links{ display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:center; }
      .links a{ color: rgba(255,255,255,.78); font-size: 14px; }
      .links a:hover{ color: rgba(255,255,255,.95); }
      .pill{
        padding: 10px 12px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,.06);
        color: rgba(255,255,255,.92) !important;
      }

      .card{
        margin: 28px 0;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,.06);
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 20px;
        box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,.45);
      }
      h1{ margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 34px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
      h2{ margin: 18px 0 8px; font-size: 18px; }
      .lead{ color: rgba(255,255,255,.72); font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 75ch; }
      .text{ color: rgba(255,255,255,.72); line-height: 1.6; }

      .grid{
        display:grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr));
        gap: 12px;
        margin-top: 14px;
      }
      .tile{
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);
        border-radius: 14px;
        padding: 14px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,.03);
      }
      ul{ margin: 8px 0 0 18px; color: rgba(255,255,255,.70); line-height: 1.55; }

      .cta{ display:flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 16px; }
      .btn{
        display:inline-flex;
        align-items:center;
        justify-content:center;
        padding: 12px 16px;
        border-radius: 14px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,.04);
        box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0,0,0,.22);
        transition: transform .12s ease, background .12s ease;
      }
      .btn:hover{ transform: translateY(-1px); background: rgba(255,255,255,.07); }
      .btn.primary{ background: rgba(255,255,255,.12); }
      .btn.ghost{ background: rgba(255,255,255,.03); }

      @media (max-width: 720px){
        .grid{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
